cc:Work.dc:title: blue flower
cc:Work.dc:description: I used random path on r*sin() and r* cos() to generate circluar paths using lindaa.map palette (from fractint) with a qbasic program that I had set to output path info in svg format. I find the svg format a little big for this and while it might be possible to generate under inkscape, I don't see an easy way.
